        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 1:58PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hagaman, or near Amsterdam, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Parkis Mills, Shaw Corners, Barkersville, West Milton, Glenwild,
Greenfield Center, Wiley Corners, North Greenfield, Porter Corners,
Corinth, West Galway, Whiteside Corners, North Milton, Fox Hill,
Randall Corner, Mount Pleasant, Frink Corner, Hagedorns Mills, South
Corinth, and Sky Ranch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
